cs.CG, cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.CC, cs.GT. 

The paper deals with computational geometry and combinatorics, specifically the problem of finding Tverberg partitions with tolerance. Therefore, cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves algorithms and complexity analysis, which suggests cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity) as likely sub-categories. The use of combinatorial techniques and graph theory in the paper makes cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper involves some game theory concepts, which suggests cs.GT (Game Theory) as a possible sub-category.
